merchant.name: Stuff'd - Funan
merchant.description:
So how would you describe Stuff'd? Factually, it would be: Mexican and Turkish-inspired street food with health options. The halal-certified, takeaway-only food business started in 2014 and at last check, it has 20 outlets across Singapore operating under franchise modelling and there are always long queues during weekday mealtimes.It's the first food business in Singapore to successfully bring Mexican and middle-eastern inspired dishes to the masses. 
Source: hungrygowhere.com
Get the latest food news there
